  "notes": "GraphicalFrequencyUncertaintyCalculatorsTests.cs itself only asserts distribution TYPE (Normal vs LogNormal) and array-length invariants -- it has no exact numeric oracle values for LessSimpleMethod's output arrays. Per the compute-then-pin convention, these cases reuse that Theory test's own inputs (exceedanceProbabilities=[0.5,0.2,0.1,0.02], stagesOrFlows=[10,15,20,30]) and pin the REAL C# GraphicalFrequencyUncertaintyCalculators.LessSimpleMethod output (filled_exceedance_probabilities/distribution_means/distribution_standard_deviations/distribution_pdf_at), verified via the oracle_emitter/verify_oracles.py gate. No RNG/seed is involved -- LessSimpleMethod is purely deterministic. distribution_pdf_at [50, 20.0] targets index 50 (exceedance probability 0.1, mean==20 for the stages case / mean==ln(20) for the flows case) specifically because it discriminates Normal vs LogNormal: PDF(20) differs sharply between the two (0.0607 vs 0.3989) even though both share the identical numeric mean/sd construction parameters at that index -- LogNormal.pdf(20) == Normal(0,1).pdf(0) == 1/sqrt(2*pi) exactly, since z=(ln(20)-ln(20))/sd==0 there. The exception-throwing tests (null/mismatched-length/insufficient-data/invalid-ERL guards) are NOT in this JSON -- they're plain CHECK_THROWS_AS assertions in test_fixtures.cpp instead, since doctest fixtures here only carry numeric oracle values, not exception expectations.",
